data.description: Located in the sought after community of Windsor Hills, this fabulous 3900+ sq ft three-story historic home is truly impressive throughout. Sitting on just over 3/4 of an acre, this stone and cedar Tudor Colonial features soaring ceilings, an abundance of natural light, and hardwood flooring throughout. Backing to Gwynns Falls Park, this urban oasis offers spectacular views of the Falls from the beautiful, covered porch stretching the entire width of the house.  Step through the charming vintage doors enhanced with crosshatch side lights and transoms into the grand entrance hall. The sizeable living room is a perfect place to entertain. Updated kitchen with generous walk-in pantry, and dual fuel gas stove with electric oven is adjacent to the double decker side porch.  Also, a full bathroom on the first floor. The wide staircase takes you past an original stained-glass window and leads to a spacious second floor landing.  The current floor plan has enormous flexibility including the potential for seven, generously sized bedrooms! The oversized (27x13) primary bedroom, created by combining two bedrooms, could easily be divided to reestablish a sixth bedroom.  The third floor is currently a spacious legal apartment. This sun-drenched retreat features an enormous family room, two generous bedrooms, bath, and an adorable kitchen with arched, crosshatched windows. Need more bedrooms? The third-floor family room could be converted to a seventh bedroom! Or the entire third floor could be transformed into the primary bedroom oasis of your dreams! Plenty of room for an office/walk-in closet/spa bath. The possibilities are endless!  The full, unfinished basement and ample closet space offer storage galore throughout this gem! Explore the Gwynns Falls biking and hiking trails and the Carrie Murray Nature Center. The NEW Cahill Recreational Center is also nearby.  All of this and a two-car parking in front of this home.   Property is being sold "As Is," but has been well maintained.
